    <description>&amp;quot;The Untold Battles of the Last War: Lots of Ogre adventure, at a bargain price.  This book includes seven complete scenarios, requiring only the basic map from Ogre/G.E.V. or Deluxe Ogre, and usable with both the original boardgame and miniatures!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This scenario book includes seven scenarios for Ogre submitted by various people for the Steve Jackson Games/Wounds Unlimited Ogre Scenario Design Contest:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    1.0 Hammer and Anvil (Alvin Helms) - &amp;quot;An Ogre stumbles into a trap... can the trap survive?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    2.0 The Black Knight (Peter Lowter) - &amp;quot;A demented Ogre holds a pass against all forces&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    3.0 DreadEx (Kevin Henson) - &amp;quot;A package must race through a wall of armor to HQ.  The carrier? Ogre express!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    4.0 Kill the Ogre (Barry Stockinger) - &amp;quot;An Ogre is being assembled on the battlefield.  Will it be destroyed before it can power up?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    5.0 Run for the Border (Chris Dellicarpini) - &amp;quot;An Ogre attempts to defect to the other side&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    6.0 Spoiling Attack (C. Andrew Walters) - &amp;quot;An armor force makes a pre-emptive strike against a hiding Ogre.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;    7.0 The Thin Line (David Valenze) - &amp;quot;Two forces clash, each hoping to hold on long enough for reinforcements to arrive.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part of the Ogre/GEV Family.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Ogre&amp;#10;    G.E.V.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For the record, there have now been three books published in this series, &amp;quot;Scenario Book 2&amp;quot; has fourteen scenarios, and &amp;quot;Scenario Book 3&amp;quot; has nine scenarios.  Both are available only as a PDF.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.sjgames.com/ogre/scenariobook2/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.sjgames.com/ogre/scenariobook3/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
